Perfect! Here's a summary of what's in commonAI.js:

📋 Contents of commonAI.js
1. Gemini Model Management
window.useGemini25 - Global flag for model preference (default: false = 1.5 Flash)
window.toggleGeminiModel() - Function to toggle between Gemini 2.5 and 1.5 Flash models
Model preference is stored in localStorage for persistence
2. Text-to-Speech Functions
window.currentSpeech - Global variable to track active speech
window.stopSpeaking() - Cancels any ongoing speech synthesis
window.speakText(text) - Converts text to speech with HTML tag removal
3. Media Capture Functions
window.captureImage(section) - Opens camera overlay for photo capture
window.recordAudio(section) - Opens microphone overlay for audio recording
window.uploadFile(e, section) - Handles file uploads (images, audio, video, PDF, documents)
4. UI Response Formatting
formatAIResponse(text) - Formats AI responses with:
Bold text (*text* → <b>text</b>)
Line breaks (\n → <br>)
Read-aloud button (🔊)
5. Navigation Management
ensureNavbarLoaded(cb) - Robust navbar loader with retry logic
Dynamically loads navbar.js if not already present
6. Gemini API Integration
getGeminiAnswer(localData, msg, apiKey, imageData) - Main function for calling Gemini API
Supports both text and image inputs
Uses backend proxy (/api/gemini) for API calls
Handles model selection (gemini-pro-vision for images, 2.5/1.5 Flash for text)
Includes error handling and response validation
All these functions are shared utilities that can be reused across multiple info sections (Home, Edu, Agro, Medi, Community, Navi, Servi, Eco) instead of being duplicated in each file! ✅